<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM, A DEEP SADNESS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28 12:06:18 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Vietnam is a deep scar, an overwhelming sadness.  I feel it deep within me, even though I was a child during Vietnam.  I often wonder what the soldiers who died there would be doing today.  Would they also show that 1000 yard stare that I have seen on other Vietnam combat veterans?<br><br>
I don't think I trust Government less.  I really have no reason to.  The Government is us.  It is everything that is good and bad about America.  We were, and should remain, a country that can help the weak, the victim; the one who can stand up to the perpetrators of the world.  Vietnam has not altered that view.  There was some good done in Vietnam.  I'm certain that most of our soldiers who went to Vietnam did not have malicious intentions.<br><br>
I hope that the Vietnam veterans are healing.  I only hope that lightness descends upon their souls and chases away the darkness and sadness that has resided there for too long.<br><br>

